The bFCA model is specified by five equations. For our application of the bFCA model, we specify communities as demand sites and HCFs as supply sites. The model includes i communities (i ∈ {1,…, N}) and j HCFs (j ∈ {1,…, J}). Equation (1) calculates the demand for ART at each HCF in the country; demand is specified in terms of the number of people living with HIV. The demand at each HCF depends upon how many communities are in its catchment area, how many people living with HIV each of these communities contain, the travel time from the HCF to each community, the mode of transportation used and the behavioral phenomenon of distance decay. It is defined by:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
